description:
Juliette Greco, born 7 February 1927, is a French actress and popular chanson singer.

Muse to the Parisian literary scene of the '50s, godmother of songwriter-led '60s French pop, and a self-reinventing torch singer from the '70s until now, Juliette Greco is one of the great French recording artists of the 20th century.
